item.title: Rmarkdown -> Blogdown -> Hugo -> Github -> Netlify
item.description: Everything seems to be up running correctly! I spent the last day or so figuring out how to get a personal website running from R studio Proof that I actually got it running library(ape) set.seed(10) par(mfrow=c(2,2)) plot(rlineage(0.1, 0)) # Yule process with lambda = 0.1 title("Yule process with lambda = 0.1") plot(rlineage(0.1, 0.05)) # simple birth-death process title("Birth death process") b <- function(t) 1/(1 + exp(0.2*t - 1)) # logistic curve(b, 0, 50, xlab = "Time", ylab = "") mu <- 0.
